properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 16 at 12:53PM EST until January 18 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to 1 mile or less. For the Small Craft Advisory,
east winds 20 to 25 kt expected.

* WHERE...Nearshore Gulf waters from the Walton-Okaloosa County
line to the Ochlockonee River out 20 nautical miles.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 4 PM EST /3 PM CST/
this afternoon. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM EST
/midnight CST/ Friday to 1 PM EST /noon CST/ Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.
